<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I often fear the debt of my sins will be collected<br>
and the price will be more then i can bare<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I lost all that i love<br>
my inspiration is gone<br>
a brisk cold wind now blows through me...<br>
even the depths of my stomach came wretching out in my despair<br>
i have only myself to question. <br>
while i did not understand the lesson to be learned from something so wonderful yet, with no future... i soon learned it was the price i must pay for my sins<br>
<br>
For another loved me. <br>
another gave me all she had... but i was not given the emotion to return to her. <br>
I betrayed her... though with no malice in heart<br>
<br>
and now the role is mine to pay the price<br>
having lost myself into something that to this day i look back on... and still feel the price may be worth it<br>
a rainbow... a muse that i could loose myself in<br>
<br>
I hope her road leads to her happiness...<br>
i wish her only the best... i just regret it was not me<br>
fate is not with out His justice it seems...<br>
and now i pray, i beg, that my debts are paid in full...<br>
<br>
I lost all i loved... but still hope... still hope... that she will loose no more... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seraphimmm>Seraphimmm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.cox.net/seraphimm/boundhandsrose.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Existant
